Privacy Policy for Dragon Security Bot
Last updated: 05/04/2025

Dragon Security Bot is committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy policy outlines the data we collect and how it is used when you interact with our bot. By using Dragon Security Bot, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

Information We Collect
When you use Dragon Security Bot, we may collect the following types of information:

Discord user data: We collect the Discord ID, username, and activity data of users who interact with the bot to provide our services (such as sending messages, performing actions like bans, and role assignments).

Server data: The bot collects information about the servers it is invited to, such as the server name, owner, and roles.

Interaction data: We may store logs of commands, actions taken, and user interactions with the bot for moderation and security purposes.

How We Use Your Data
The data we collect is used solely for the following purposes:

To provide the bot’s functionality (such as moderation, anti-nuke protection, etc.)

To improve the bot’s features and services.

To respond to user inquiries or issues.

Data Sharing and Third Parties
Dragon Security Bot does not share your personal information with any third parties, except in the case of legal requirements or as necessary to provide the service.

Data Retention
We retain user data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose of providing the bot’s services. Logs and user interactions may be kept for up to [insert duration] to maintain performance and security.

Your Rights
You have the right to:

Request the deletion of your data from our records by contacting us at [insert support email].

Review the information we have collected about you.

Security
We take security seriously and implement reasonable measures to protect your data. However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute protection.

Contact Us
If you have any questions about this privacy policy or the data we collect, please contact us at [ytmuzammilop@gmail.com].
